<br>
I don't know you, but let me assure you, Siffo is far from greedy.  <br>
<br>
He didn't come here with his question about whether or not it would be an effective shield for a rogue and and admit that he rolled on the shield so that you could take it upon yourself to attack him as being greedy.   <br>
<br>
He did it because he genuinely wanted to learn whether or not he was justified in rolling on the shield and to get feedback on whether or not his thoughts on how he might use it have any merit.<br>
<br>
Trust me, if Siffo had won the roll and discovered that it was worthless to him, he WOULD NOT have put it up for sell in the bazaar.  He would have immediately done what was right.<br>
